{"type":"text","timestamp":1780128915369,"sessionID":"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND","part":{"id":"prt_e77f39fa2001netfP5IWx10PWS","messageID":"msg_e77f376b0001Agt6iv38MiDEgC","sessionID":"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND","type":"text","text":"\n\nNow let me check the prior iteration files and the spec to understand the research trajectory:\n","time":{"start":1780128915362,"end":1780128915364}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780128915631,"sessionID":"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_fx7kciwu8yyz_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Phase 001: Skill-benchmark deep research (multi-model)\"\n3: description: \"20-iteration multi-model deep research (5x MiniMax-2.7, 5x DeepSeek-v4-pro, 5x GPT-5.5-xhigh-fast, 5x Opus-4.8-native) investigating Lane C skill-benchmark design and the deep-agent-improvement->deep-improvement rename impact map.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"skill-benchmark deep research\"\n6:   - \"122 phase 001\"\n7:   - \"multi-model deep research skill benchmark\"\n8: importance_tier: \"important\"\n9: contextType: \"research\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Authored research-phase spec; preparing multi-model deep-research runs\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Run /deep:start-research-loop:auto per model (5 iters each) into research/\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     completion_pct: 5\n19:     open_questions: []\n20:     answered_questions: []\n21: ---\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n23: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n24: \n25: # Phase 001 — Skill-benchmark deep research\n26: \n27: **Parent:** `122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode`\n28: **Type:** Deep-research phase (informs design of Lane C + the rename)\n29: **Status:** Active\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 1. Purpose\n34: \n35: Run a multi-model deep-research loop to answer the open questions that gate the design of **Lane C (skill-benchmark)** and to produce an exhaustive **rename impact map** for `deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement`. Findings feed Phase 002 (rename) and Phase 003 (Lane C design + build).\n36: \n37: Research only — no implementation. Per the deep-research contract: report findings, cite sources, never implement fixes during research.\n38: \n39: ## 2. Research questions\n40: \n41: Derived from parent `spec.md` §11 (OQ1–OQ6) and §7 (R1–R6):\n42: \n43: - **RQ1.** What are the right scoring dimensions + weights for benchmarking a skill's *real-world utilization* (routing accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency, usefulness/ablation, structural connectivity)? How are they normalized across skills of different shapes?\n44: - **RQ2.** How do you build a credible **hint-free dispatch harness** that runs a realistic scenario against an AI and captures *which references/assets it loaded* and its tool trace — without leaking the expected answer into the prompt?\n45: - **RQ3.** Should activation accuracy be scored against the skill-advisor, the in-`SKILL.md` smart router, or both (as separate sub-scores)? What does \"properly utilized\" mean operationally?\n46: - **RQ4.** Scenario/fixture authoring: hand-authored vs generated-from-the-skill's-own-triggers — how to get realistic coverage while avoiding circularity (scoring a skill against scenarios derived from itself)?\n47: - **RQ5.** How should the **Skill Benchmark Report** rank bottlenecks and express remediations so a follow-up packet (or Lane A) can act on them?\n48: - **RQ6.** Exhaustive rename surface for `deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement` and a safe ordering: skill dir, `SKILL.md` frontmatter/triggers, commands, agent + runtime mirrors (`.claude`/`.codex`/`.gemini`), skill-advisor graph (`skill-graph.json`), `descriptions.json`, sentinel `sk-prompt-models`, root docs/CLAUDE.md, and any tests/fixtures.\n49: - **RQ7.** Prior art: how do agent/skill frameworks elsewhere measure tool/skill *discoverability* and routing efficiency (retrieval precision/recall, ablation, LLM-as-judge), and what transfers here?\n50: \n51: ## 3. Method — multi-model split\n52: \n53: Run via the canonical loop only: `/deep:start-research-loop` (YAML owns dispatch, state, convergence, synthesis). Packet-local state under `001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/`.\n54: \n55: **20 iterations, executor split (5/5/5/5):**\n56: \n57: | Iterations | Model | Executor route |\n58: | ---------- | ----- | -------------- |\n59: | 1–5 | MiniMax-2.7 | `cli-opencode` |\n60: | 6–10 | DeepSeek-v4-pro | `cli-opencode` (DeepSeek API / opencode-go) |\n61: | 11–15 | GPT-5.5 (xhigh reasoning, fast) | `cli-codex` |\n62: | 16–20 | Opus-4.8 | native `@deep-research` |\n63: \n64: Per small-model dispatch rule, MiniMax-2.7 and DeepSeek-v4-pro dispatch consults `sk-prompt-models` (provider/quota/context-budget). Per CLI dispatch rule, the relevant `cli-*/SKILL.md` is read before composing executor prompts.\n65: \n66: Iteration discipline (from deep-research contract): LEAF, one focus per iteration, 8–11 tool calls (max 12), externalize findings to `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, append JSONL delta with `newInfoRatio`, cite every finding.\n67: \n68: ## 4. Deliverables\n69: \n70: - `research/research.md` — synthesized findings answering RQ1–RQ7.\n71: - `research/deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, dashboard — workflow-owned state.\n72: - A convergence report (stop reason, iterations, questions-answered ratio, newInfoRatio trend).\n73: - A rename impact map (RQ6) consumable by Phase 002.\n74: \n75: ## 5. Success criteria\n76: \n77: - Loop reaches convergence or 20 iterations with consistent state files.\n78: - The 5/5/5/5 model split is executed and recorded in iteration provenance.\n79: - `research/research.md` answers each RQ with cited sources and per-iteration ruled-out directions.\n80: - Findings are concrete enough to drive Phase 002 (rename) and Phase 003 (Lane C design).\n81: \n82: ## 6. Out of scope\n83: \n84: No implementation, no skill mutation, no rename execution (that is Phase 002). This phase produces evidence and recommendations only.\n\n(End of file - total 84 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Phase 001: Skill-benchmark deep research (multi-model)\"\ndescription: \"20-iteration multi-model deep research (5x MiniMax-2.7, 5x DeepSeek-v4-pro, 5x GPT-5.5-xhigh-fast, 5x Opus-4.8-native) investigating Lane C skill-benchmark design and the deep-agent-improvement->deep-improvement rename impact map.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"skill-benchmark deep research\"\n  - \"122 phase 001\"\n  - \"multi-model deep research skill benchmark\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"research\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored research-phase spec; preparing multi-model deep-research runs\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Run /deep:start-research-loop:auto per model (5 iters each) into research/\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 5\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1780128915618,"end":1780128915629}},"id":"prt_e77f39fa7001eW2W7UvP4waWnl","sessionID":"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND","messageID":"msg_e77f376b0001Agt6iv38MiDEgC"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780128915883,"sessionID":"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_fx7kciwu8yyz_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-003.out"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-003.out</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \u001b[93m\u001b[1m! \u001b[0m agent \"general\" is a subagent, not a primary agent. Falling back to default agent\n2: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1780128890816,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f33fbc001zl9dElwdIUg3TV\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f32b4d001iXCdjrHgTVnzx2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"snapshot\":\"bf929e93d345be736680fb39ed9c37e71ede4468\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n3: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1780128894479,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f34e0a001BSK4FrG45gn6K6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f32b4d001iXCdjrHgTVnzx2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nI'll research RQ3 (activation scoring: skill-advisor vs smart router) and RQ4 (fixture authoring avoiding circularity) for Lane C design. Let me gather ground-truth from the repo.\\n\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780128894474,\"end\":1780128894476}}}\n4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128894915,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_a31gbemw6wx3_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-agent-improvement\\n3: description: \\\"Evaluator-first bounded agent improvement: 5-dim scoring, dynamic profiling, packet-local candidates, guarded promotion.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 1.9.0.0\\n6: triggers:\\n7:   - deep-agent-improvement\\n8:   - agent improvement loop\\n9:   - bounded agent improvement\\n10:   - 5-dimension scoring\\n11:   - integration scanner\\n12:   - dynamic profiling\\n13:   - model-benchmark mode\\n14:   - benchmark a model or prompt framework\\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: <!-- Keywords: deep-agent-improvement, deep-agent-improvement, agent-improvement, benchmark-harness, score-candidate, promote-candidate, rollback-candidate -->\\n18: \\n19: # Recursive Agent: Evaluator-First Improvement Orchestrator\\n20: \\n21: Evaluator-first workflow for testing whether a bounded agent surface can be improved without immediately mutating the source of truth. It combines packet-local candidates, deterministic scoring, repeatable benchmarks, and explicit promotion or rollback gates.\\n22: \\n23: ---\\n24: \\n25: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n26: \\n27: ### Two Co-Equal Lanes\\n28: \\n29: This skill supports two co-equal use-case lanes that share the same candidate, dispatcher, and scorer seams:\\n30: \\n31: | Lane | Pick when | Command |\\n32: | --- | --- | --- |\\n33: | **Lane A: Agent-Improvement** | You want to improve a bounded agent `.md` file | `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` |\\n34: | **Lane B: Model-Benchmark** | You want to be... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128895316,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_a31gbemw6wx3_2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: system-skill-advisor\\n3: description: Routes non-trivial requests to matching skills through standalone MCP metadata and stable advisor tool ids.\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep]\\n5: version: 0.1.0\\n6: trigger_phrases:\\n7:   - \\\"skill advisor\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"gate 2 routing\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"advisor_recommend\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"advisor_status\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"which skill should handle this\\\"\\n12:   - \\\"route this request to a skill\\\"\\n13:   - \\\"system skill advisor\\\"\\n14: keywords:\\n15:   - skill-routing\\n16:   - gate-2\\n17:   - advisor-mcp\\n18:   - legacy-tool-bridge\\n19:   - skill-graph\\n20:   - semantic-lane\\n21: intent_signals:\\n22:   - \\\"Gate 2 skill routing\\\"\\n23:   - \\\"advisor_recommend native MCP routing\\\"\\n24:   - \\\"advisor_status freshness check\\\"\\n25:   - \\\"which skill should handle this request\\\"\\n26:   - \\\"run the skill advisor hook\\\"\\n27: ---\\n28: \\n29: <!-- Keywords: system-skill-advisor, skill-advisor, advisor_recommend, advisor_status, advisor_rebuild, advisor_validate, skill_graph_scan, skill_graph_query, skill_graph_status, skill_graph_validate, skill_graph_propagate_enhances, cross-skill-edges, gate-2-routing, standalone-mcp, legacy-tool-bridge, skill-graph -->\\n30: \\n31: # System Skill Advisor\\n32: \\n33: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_md -->\\n34: \\n35: Routes non-trivial user requests to the right skill through the standalone Skill Advisor MCP package.\\n36: \\n37: ---\\n38: \\n39: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n40: \\n41: Use this skill when the work is a... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n6: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128895654,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_a31gbemw6wx3_3\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: sk-doc\\n3: description: \\\"Markdown and OpenCode component specialist: doc quality, content optimization, component scaffolds, install guides, playbooks.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Bash, Edit, Glob, Grep, Read, Task, Write]\\n5: version: 1.5.0.0\\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: <!-- Keywords: sk-doc, markdown-quality, skill-creation, document-validation, ascii-flowchart, llms-txt, content-optimization, extract-structure -->\\n9: \\n10: # Documentation Creation Specialist - Unified Markdown & Component Management\\n11: \\n12: Unified specialist providing: (1) Document quality pipeline with structure enforcement and content optimization, (2) OpenCode component creation (skills, agents, commands) with scaffolding, validation and packaging, (3) ASCII flowchart creation for visualizing workflows, (4) Install guide creation for setup documentation and (5) Feature catalog and manual testing playbook creation for inventory and validation packages.\\n13: \\n14: **Core Principle**: Structure first, then content, then quality.\\n15: \\n16: **Architecture**: Scripts handle deterministic parsing/metrics. AI handles quality judgment and recommendations.\\n17: \\n18: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\\n19: \\n20: ### Use Case: Document Quality Management\\n21: \\n22: Enforce markdown structure, optimize content for AI assistants, validate quality through script-assisted AI analysis.\\n23: \\n24: **README Creation** - Use `readme_template.md` + `readme_creation.md` when:\\n25: - Creating new README for any folder or project\\n26: - User requests \\\"create a RE... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n7: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1780128895963,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f353d8001Eo7m73rWVSWyt8\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"f56995973698e7b9c82c7c113be6f3847a125a1d\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f32b4d001iXCdjrHgTVnzx2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":36002,\"input\":33702,\"output\":491,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":1809}},\"cost\":0.01080834}}\n8: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1780128898667,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f35e68001SC1Ki633yhwacy\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f354d3001DTrUVoFXD5y4M5\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"snapshot\":\"01384b354ac856d140800f88d594fd0b77c35cfe\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n9: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128899861,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_l06tnp5un5cu_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/description.json\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/description.json</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: {\\n2:   \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode\\\",\\n3:   \\\"description\\\": \\\"Phase parent (complete, 19 phases): two-arc program adding a model-benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement (build arc 001-007) and elevating it to a co-equal lane (two-lane arc 008-018), plus a doc + changelog closeout (019).\\\",\\n4:   \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n5:     \\\"deep-agent-improvement\\\",\\n6:     \\\"model-benchmark\\\",\\n7:     \\\"two-lane\\\",\\n8:     \\\"phase-parent\\\",\\n9:     \\\"benchmark-mode\\\"\\n10:   ],\\n11:   \\\"lastUpdated\\\": \\\"2026-05-30T08:35:00Z\\\",\\n12:   \\\"specId\\\": \\\"121\\\",\\n13:   \\\"folderSlug\\\": \\\"deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode\\\",\\n14:   \\\"parentChain\\\": [],\\n15:   \\\"memorySequence\\\": 1,\\n16:   \\\"memoryNameHistory\\\": [\\n17:     \\\"29-05-26_17-02__delivered-the-complete-two-lane-experience-for.md\\\"\\n18:   ]\\n19: }\\n\\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"{\\n  \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Phase parent (complete, 19 phases): two-arc program adding a model-benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement (build arc 001-007) and elevating it to a co-equal lane (two-lane arc 008-018), plus a doc + changelog closeout (019).\\\",\\n  \\\"keywords\\\": [\\n    \\\"deep-agent-improvement\\\",\\n    \\\"model-benchmark\\\",\\n    \\\"two-lane\\\",\\n    \\\"phase-parent\\\",\\n    \\\"benchmark-mode\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"lastUpdated\\\":... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128900150,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_function_l06tnp5un5cu_2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/**/*\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-003.out\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/logs/iter-002.out\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/orchestration-status.log\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/logs/iter-002.out\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/gpt55/state-parts/iter-002.jsonl\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n11: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1780128900434,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f36550001iolyeF9PVe6Obb\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"e008bbad453d1a1918f619ab96595daf9d222dc3\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f354d3001DTrUVoFXD5y4M5\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":56792,\"input\":21143,\"output\":141,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":35508}},\"cost\":0.00864258}}\n12: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1780128902077,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e77f36bba001uBO2qOqOJAPhyK\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f36659001BU7ptanhUEFcTV\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"snapshot\":\"3f81ddaf40d053159eb38a9196a7cda68975fb21\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128903012,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_7xllavgzls6o_1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/iterations/iteration-001.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/iterations/iteration-001.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Iteration 001 — RQ1 Scoring Dimensions + RQ7 Prior Art (MiniMax-2.7)\\n2: \\n3: ## Focus\\n4: RQ1: Define the scoring dimensions for benchmarking a skill's real-world utilization — routing/activation accuracy, unprompted reference/asset discovery, efficiency/bottlenecks, usefulness via skill-on/skill-off ablation, and structural connectivity (orphan refs, dead router keys). Plus RQ7: external prior art on tool/skill discoverability and routing evaluation (retrieval precision/recall, tool-selection accuracy, ablation, LLM-as-judge, agent-eval harnesses).\\n5: \\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: ## Actions Taken\\n9: \\n10: 1. **Read deep-agent-improvement SKILL.md** — mapped the skill's two co-equal lanes (Agent-Improvement / Model-Benchmark), three pluggable seams (candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer), smart router (INTENT_SIGNALS, RESOURCE_MAP, RUNTIME_ASSETS), lane-aware references/assets organization, loop-host.cjs entry point with `--mode` flag, and the 5-dimension scoring rubric.\\n11: 2. **Read sk-doc SKILL.md and system-skill-advisor SKILL.md** — confirmed sk-doc validates doc shape/package-structure, and system-skill-advisor routes requests externally at ≥0.8 confidence. Lane C is positioned as distinct from both.\\n12: 3. **Reviewed sibling packet 121-deep... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n14: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128903501,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_7xllavgzls6o_2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/state-parts/iter-001.jsonl\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/state-parts/iter-001.jsonl</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: {\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"model\\\":\\\"minimax\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.6,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"iter1\\\"}\\n\\n(End of file - total 1 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"iteration\\\":1,\\\"model\\\":\\\"minimax\\\",\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.6,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"iter1\\\"}\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/minimax/state-parts/iter-001.jsonl\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780128903495,\"end\":1780128903500}},\"id\":\"prt_e77f36f5b001S9LTqoQgmLKP4K\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e77f36659001BU7ptanhUEFcTV\"}}\n15: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780128903985,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1880cd6beffeAAFH1uk95wMSND\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_function_7